<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870928-0162 </DOCNO><HL> J. Baker Share Net to Decline</HL><DD> 09/28/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> JBAK </IN><DATELINE> BOSTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   J. Baker Inc., a shoe retailer, said it expects earnings for its third quarter ending Nov. 1 to be down slightly from the restated year-earlier 23 cents a share.    August sales trailed those in the year-earlier month because of a late back-to-school period and &quot;general softness of sales in the footwear industry,&quot; the company said. But it added that total sales in the fiscal third quarter are expected to exceed the $49.1 million a year earlier. </TEXT></DOC>